{"type":"message","id":"8fccef18","parentId":"0fa2ee1e","timestamp":"2026-02-19T18:46:34.155Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing Directory Structures**\n\nI'm currently reviewing the file system, particularly the `src` directory, and it seems I need to adjust my approach. I've noted the difference between the existing `src/knowledge_base.py` file and the desired `src/knowledge_base/long_term_memory.md` location. This necessitates a correction in my plans.\n\n\n**Refining the Path Forward**\n\nNow I am going to try to create the `src/knowledge_base/long_term_memory.md` file, as instructed. Then I will write `src/knowledge_base/api_performance.md` using the simulated search. I will also create the `docs/ARCHITECTURE_MANIFESTO.md` file. I'm focusing on organizing these files as requested.\n\n\n**Constructing the Knowledge Base**\n\nI've successfully created the `src/knowledge_base` directory, as well as `src/knowledge_base/long_term_memory.md`, which is now populated. I've also drafted the `src/knowledge_base/api_performance.md` file, which includes initial content on API performance optimization. Furthermore, I created `docs/ARCHITECTURE_MANIFESTO.md`, which is also now populated as instructed. I am proceeding as planned.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771526794152_49","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"docs/ARCHITECTURE_MANIFESTO.md","content":"# ARCHITECTURE MANIFESTO: VISIONARY UPGRADE (SELF-EVOLUTION)\n\n## Analysis: Thinking vs. Speed\n*   **Thinking (LLM):** High Latency (2-5s). Good for strategy, complex decisions, error recovery.\n*   **Rust (HFT):** Ultra-Low Latency (0.002ms). Essential for execution, parsing, rate limiting.\n\n## Verdict\n*   **Brain (Arkady):** Strategy, Risk Management, Code Generation, Self-Healing.\n*   **Muscle (Rust/Code):** Trade Execution, Signature, WebSocket parsing, Rate Limiting.\n\n## Justification\nMoney loves speed (Rust), but Survival loves wisdom (LLM).\n"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Formulating the Initial Structure**\n\nI've decided to start by making the `src/knowledge_base` directory to hold `long_term_memory.md`, and then proceed with creating `api_performance.md` in the same directory. I've also composed the `ARCHITECTURE_MANIFESTO.md` file in the docs directory, which is ready to go. I am now proceeding with the planned file creation.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771526794153_50","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Long Term Memory\n\nThis file serves as the long-term memory store for the agentic system.\nIt acts as a persistent knowledge base for \"Arkady\" (The Brain).\n\n## Structure\n- Strategies\n- Lessons Learned\n- Critical Context\n","file_path":"src/knowledge_base/long_term_memory.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771526794153_51","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# API Performance Best Practices\n\n## JSON Parsing\n*   **simdjson:** Use for critical hot paths. It is significantly faster than standard `json`.\n*   **orjson:** Good alternative for Python speedups.\n\n## Buffer Management\n*   **Reuse Buffers:** Avoid allocating new buffers for every message. Reusing memory reduces GC overhead and latency.\n\n## Recommendations\n1.  Prioritize Rust-based parsers in the hot loop.\n2.  Minimize object creation in WebSocket handlers.\n","file_path":"src/knowledge_base/api_performance.md"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":136330,"output":1236,"cacheRead":132096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137566,"cost":{"input":0.27266,"output":0.014832,"cacheRead":0.026419200000000004,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.31391120000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771526765920}}
